body:
OK got it. The reason for this is that the current default version of the docs is r0.12 (which should also be the version you get if you use pip to install tensorflow).

If you look at the [master version of the docs](https://www.tensorflow.org/versions/master/get_started/os_setup) instead, it should be up to date with the master version of the code.
